this basically works, but is definitely getting trapped in local optima :(
e.g.  2.in currently gets 719 but earlier randomly ordered horizontal jiggerpokery found a 718
random was able to get 718 even with search_max=5

perf ideas?
    change HashMap<(isize, isize), _> to Vec<Option<_>>
        Option<> is fine since we don't think we're memory constrained
        we need to key by just non-rotor, non-edge bits of each column
        similar to how we have c2_raw right now, the key should be bit concat of c0_raw and c1_raw
    reorder loops
        right now it's c0+c1 pair, then c2
        if we instead do c2 on the outside we don't have to assemble cols_next except for the actual winner
            we just track best c0 (and maybe pointer to data for it) and then deal with it at the end
        this might also let us easily/quickly parallelize over c2
    "live" bool could probably be 1-bit integer since we're converting both from that and back to that
